TITLE: Basic Markdoc Usage in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates the core functionality of Markdoc by parsing, transforming, and rendering a simple Markdown document to HTML. This example shows the three main steps in the Markdoc processing pipeline.
SOURCE: https://github.com/markdoc/docs/blob/main/pages/index.md#2025-04-23_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import Markdoc from '@markdoc/markdoc';

const doc = `
# Hello world.
> My first Markdoc page
`;

const ast = Markdoc.parse(doc);

const content = Markdoc.transform(ast);

const html = Markdoc.renderers.html(content);
```

