TITLE: Implementing Custom Tag Validation in Markdoc Config
DESCRIPTION: This example shows how to implement custom validation for a 'provider' tag in the Markdoc config. It checks if the tag has exactly one child and returns an error if not. This demonstrates how to extend Markdoc's validation capabilities for specific tags.
SOURCE: https://github.com/markdoc/docs/blob/main/pages/docs/validation.md#2025-04-23_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
/** @type {import('@markdoc/markdoc').Config} */
const config = {
  tags: {
    provider: {
      render: 'Provider',
      // ...
      validate(node) {
        if (node.children.length !== 1) {
          return [
            {
              id: 'provider-children',
              level: 'critical',
              message: 'Providers must only have one child.'
            }
          ];
        }
        return [];
      }
    }
  }
};
```

