TITLE: Creating a Table of Contents in Markdoc
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to create a table of contents in Markdoc by collecting headings from the page content and rendering them in a list. It includes a function to collect headings and a React component to render the table of contents.
SOURCE: https://github.com/markdoc/docs/blob/main/pages/docs/examples/index.md#2025-04-23_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
function collectHeadings(node, sections = []) {
  if (node) {
    // Match all h1, h2, h3â€¦ tags
    if (node.name.match(/h\d/)) {
      const title = node.children[0];

      if (typeof title === 'string') {
        sections.push({
          ...node.attributes,
          title
        });
      }
    }

    if (node.children) {
      for (const child of node.children) {
        collectHeadings(child, sections);
      }
    }
  }

  return sections;
}

const content = Markdoc.transform(ast);
const headings = collectHeadings(content);
```

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
function TableOfContents({ headings }) {
  const items = headings.filter((item) => [2, 3].includes(item.level));

  return (
    <nav>
      <ul>
        {items.map((item) => (
          <li key={item.title}>
            <a href={`#${item.id}`}>{item.title}</a>
          </li>
        ))}
      </ul>
    </nav>
  );
}
```

